  "status": "Draft",
  "summary": "This ERC defines a standard interface for oracle contracts that use multi-agent councils to resolve arbitrary information queries. It enables dApps to request resolutions, general information arbitration, and build consensus and validation in a trust-minimized way, with agents submitting answers to the queries on-chain. The ERC works by a requester opening a query to be resolved. The contract then emits the RequestCreated event with parameters specifying the query, number of infoAgents, commit deadline, and reward/bond amounts, specifications, and capabilities required. A commit phase is initiated where InfoAgents can participate by staking the required bond and submitting a hash of the answer to the query as a commit. After the quorum of infoAgents have committed, the reveal process is in",
  "title": "Agent Council Oracles"
}